comment: Oof, a friend of mine saw someone die today at work. =/
Well he does security for this company, but one of the employees there collapsed in the hallway and died of a heart attack.
He had to keep the hallway clear as the EMTs tried to revive the guy.
Yeah, it hit my friend pretty hard.
that's balls.. EMTs are good people. Not all heros wear capes.
The guy was only 41, and was physically fit, had just got done working out shortly before it happened.
just goes to show, even completely healthy people fall victim to life..
my condolences to your friend, bro
had to have been hard to watch that
Yeah, to get his mind off of it we went and saw Captain Marvel, twas very good.
Yeah, they even review the cameras, watched to see if there was any sign of anything wrong before the guy had his heart attack. That probably didn't help.
I could only guess the guy must have had some diagnosed heart condition.
I try to accept that I could drop dead tomorrow too, nothing we can do about it, we are all going to die one day.
Except Tom, since apparently he's immortal. :P
Guess it's best to go quickly. Most likely a Heart Attack is what's going to kill me. Unless there is some magical medical breakthrough before then.
yaeh lol lucky bastard.. or perhaps unlucky considering he has to deal with waves and waves of fans with the continous repeat every time the fandom dies and comes back
Both my father's parent's died of heart attacks, both my parents deal with blood pressure issues. So it runs in the family.
parents* I dunno why I made it possessive. :P
maybe they were possessive? Inner turmoil of Torque.. we'll never know..
But luckily, that's pretty much the only genetic health problems my family has, aside from some anxiety issues, but who does have anxiety issues these days?
I mean.. I don't think I do. I don't know exactly what it's like to have it or how it feels
Mine comes and goes, I've just got better at controlling it.
Rarely does it get bad, and usually only during the winter months.
Well, most of my father's anxiety issue is because he worked as a cop for 20 years, and saw a lot of shit, and before that he was a Medic in the Air Force.
be a medic in some branch of military for long enough, you gonna see some shit.
He probably saw more shit as a cop though. At least that where I've heard most of his stories. He was the police officer that went to the scenes and took pictures.
I would not be able to do that job
Yeah, my friend today said they had an officer there doing that with the person who had the heart attack.
I hope your friend gets his groove back soon, that kinda stuff will kill it for a while
Yeah, they are going to be offering counseling for the people that were involved in this.
and his boss has called to check up on him, and apparently quite a few people were asking if he was alright after he had left work.
offered to let him take the day off, my but friend refused, because they were already had it hard enough with staffing issues, and he didn't want to contribute to that.
well just keep him close and don't let him overstress or overwork.
